{
  "stem": "3331.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The new teacher's name was Wadislaw Wishnewsky.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was a reserve officer of the Polish army, and he became a teacher.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he probably never encountered Jewish boys, with peyos, with yarmulkes, and he didn't like it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he got together four classes of the Jewish boys, and he put a teacher-- a Polish teacher-- we used to call her the [NON-ENGLISH] because she was very tall-- 'the long one'-- not to let out the children.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, he came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had in one hand-- one hand was a white glove, the other hand he had a clipper.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he went from-- he went from boy to boy, and he cut off one earlock, because all the children have earlocks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He cut off one earlock, from the earlock to the middle of the head.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because he understood, if they will come home with one earlock, the parents will cut off the second earlock.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because, after all-- and he started it, one after [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had four classes, and the four classes probably had about 60 or 80 Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "All the Jewish children started to cry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were seven, eight years old.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was, in this time, seven or eight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when he came closer to me, and I saw all my friends are starting to cry, but behind me was sitting Moishele.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Moishele was the son of the [? dayan, ?] of the assistant rabbi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Moishele had the longest peyos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had peyos that they reached him to the waist.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I couldn't imagine that Moishele would go home with one [? peye. ?] I even didn't do it maybe so much for me as for Moishele.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was always a reb-- a rebel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I always stood up--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Even at seven.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
